# Mintlify Documentation

Documentation lives in `docs/` and uses Mintlify with MDX.

## MDX File Structure

Every `.mdx` file requires YAML frontmatter:

```mdx
---
title: "Page Title"
description: "Brief description for SEO and previews"
---
```

## Common Components

### Cards

```mdx
<Card title="Title" icon="icon-name" href="/path">
  Description text
</Card>

<CardGroup cols={2}>
  <Card title="..." icon="..." href="...">...</Card>
  <Card title="..." icon="..." href="...">...</Card>
</CardGroup>

<Columns cols={2}>
  <Card>...</Card>
  <Card>...</Card>
</Columns>
```

### Accordions

```mdx
<AccordionGroup>
  <Accordion icon="github" title="Accordion Title">
    Content here
  </Accordion>
</AccordionGroup>
```

### Callouts

```mdx
<Tip>Helpful tips</Tip>
<Note>Important information</Note>
<Warning>Caution notices</Warning>
```

## Navigation

Edit `docs/docs.json` to update navigation:
- Add pages to `navigation.tabs[].groups[].pages[]`
- Reference pages without `.mdx` extension
- Use relative paths from docs root (e.g., `"essentials/markdown"`)

## Structure

```
docs/
├── docs.json          # Site config & navigation
├── index.mdx          # Home page
├── quickstart.mdx     # Getting started
├── essentials/        # Core documentation
├── api-reference/     # API docs
└── images/            # Static assets
```
